article.description: The Orlando Magic did not need Tracy  McGrady to send the Denver Nuggets to their seventh consecutive loss, 89-80.
article.headline: Garrity, Kemp make up for missing McGrady
article.linkText: Magic's Garrity, Kemp pick up slack for ailing McGrady
article.story:
DENVER (AP) -- Playing without NBA scoring leader Tracy McGrady, the Orlando Magic needed something extra from everyone else.
Kemp

Garrity

Pat Garrity and Shawn Kemp scored 17 points each as the Magic overcame the absence of McGrady to defeat Denver 89-80 Friday night, sending the Nuggets to their seventh straight loss. "We all have to step up,'' Garrity said. "That's 30 points to fill playing without him.'' "Other guys have to make shots, and I think Grant (Hill) did a great job of leading the team and getting guys shots,'' Garrity said. Hill had 16 points and Mike Miller 15 for the Magic, who have beaten Denver 11 straight times. McGrady watched the game from the bench due to a lower back contusion. "Our thinking was that with his back still sore, we have to get him to 100 percent and rested him yesterday with no practice,'' Orlando coach Doc Rivers said. "My whole thinking was to try to get this win without him and we have four days to try to get him healthy.'' Juwan Howard had 20 points, Rodney White added 16 and Donnell Harvey 15 for the Nuggets. "We have no margin for error and everything has to be right all the time,'' Denver coach Jeff Bzdelik said. "We outrebounded them (48-33), but we had 20 turnovers and had good shots, but didn't finish them.'' Hill made a layup to cap an 8-0 run and give Orlando a 70-65 lead. White closed the gap to 72-70 with a jumper and 3-pointer before Miller gave the Magic some breathing room with two 3-pointers in a span of a minute to put them ahead 78-72. "They were big,'' said Miller of his 3-pointers. "I wasn't making the shots I wanted to make so I had to step up and do something like making a couple of shots down the stretch.'' Garrity made a 3-pointer with 2:08 left and two free throws with 39 seconds remaining to put Orlando ahead 83-74. White converted two free throws and a hook shot three minutes into the second half to give Denver a 52-49 lead, but Garrity and Miller hit 3-pointers over the next two minutes for Orlando. Darrell Armstrong's jumper with 4:55 left gave the Magic their last lead of the quarter as Ryan Bowen came off the bench to finish two fast breaks with layups as Denver outscored Orlando 9-5 the rest of the period to lead 63-62. Howard sank his first five shots as the Nuggets led 10-4. Kemp went 5-for-5 from the line and scored nine points for Orlando, but Howard's layup and Mark Blount's jumper that beat the buzzer cut the Magic's lead to 23-22. After two free throws by Jacque Vaughn put Orlando ahead 27-22, Howard capped an 8-0 run for the Nuggets with his first basket of the second quarter. Armstrong tied the game at 38-38 with a free throw after a technical on Bzdelik, but the Nuggets led 42-40 at halftime on two jumpers by Vincent Yarbrough in the last 2:10 of the second quarter. "We are just going to keep swinging until we get it right,'' Bzdelik said. "That is all we can do.''

Game notes
Orlando hasn't lost to Denver since March 12, 1996. ... The Magic have used 11 different starting lineups. ... The Magic finished their four-game road trip 2-2. ... Denver waived forward Art Long and activated guard Predrag Savovic. ... Guard Chris Whitney was placed on injured reserve after an MRI revealed a bone bruise in his left ankle. ... Newly acquired Mark Bryant was a no-show and won't make the trip to Los Angeles when the Nuggets play the Clippers on Saturday. ... Bzdelik got his second technical of the year.
